<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-181-131 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 569 384</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  April 9 1991 v5 n14 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Macweek 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Colorgetter resolution rises. (Optronics' Colorgetter Plusscanner) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McManus, Neil.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Optronics Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Optronics ColorGetter Plus (Digitizer) (Product introduction)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Equipment and supplies).andO;Topic:     Scanning DevicesColorProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Neil McManusandM;Chelmsford, Mass.andP;  -- Optronics now is shipping a new, higher-resolutionmodel of the company's table-top color drum scanner.andM;The Colorgetter Plus, available for less than $80,000, offers user-selectableresolutions of up to 4,064 raster lines per inch.andM;Priced at about $70,000, the original Colorgetter has resolutions of up to2,032 raster lines per inch.andM;The two Colorgetter models scan both transparent and reflective art at 12bits per color or 4,096 gray levels.andM;Both scanners can handle images in sizes ranging from 35mm slides to10-by-14-inch art.andM;Artwork is taped to clear or opaque rotating drums, both of which areincluded.andP;  The Colorgetter scanners use three multiplier tube sensors tocapture RGB (red, green, blue) data in a single pass.andM;In addition, for Macintosh users of the scanners, Optronics is offeringColorRight 2.0 software priced at $4,500.andM;The ColorRight 2.0 software allows users to review and manipulate12-bit-per-channel (36-bit) color images without rescanning.andP;  It also givesusers control over darkness and lightness of scanned images and allowsindependent balancing of RGB channels.andP;  Images can be saved as TIFF files.andM;The Colorgetter scanners hook up to the Mac through a General PurposeInterface Bus (GPIB) interface.andP;  Optronics bundles a GPIB NuBus card with theColorRight 2.0 software.andM;Optronics is at 7 Stuart Road, Chelmsford, Mass.andP;  01824.andP;  Phone (508)256-4511; fax (508) 256-1872.andO;</TEXT></DOC>